# Geocoder backends.
#
# Production path: LocationIQ (paid managed Nominatim+Photon equivalent).
# When LOCATIONIQ_API_KEY is set, both /api/geocode/search and
# /api/boundary/{osm_id} are served by LocationIQ and the public Photon/
# Nominatim composite is NOT instantiated. This is the only safe option for
# a public deployment — the free public instances will ban you under load.
#
# Sign up at https://locationiq.com, generate an access token, and drop it in
# below. Free tier is 5k requests/day; paid plans scale from there.
#
# LOCATIONIQ_API_KEY=pk.your_access_token_here
# LOCATIONIQ_BASE_URL=https://us1.locationiq.com/v1
# LOCATIONIQ_USER_AGENT=thermotree/0.1 (contact: you@example.com)
#
# Dev fallback: when LOCATIONIQ_API_KEY is unset/empty, search runs through
# Photon (autocomplete-grade prefix matching) and boundary retrieval runs
# through Nominatim (relation -> polygon). All four variables below are
# OPTIONAL — the backend ships with defaults pointing at the public
# instances. Override to point at self-hosted services or to set a User-Agent
# that complies with each provider's usage policy.
#
# NOMINATIM_BASE_URL=https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org
# NOMINATIM_USER_AGENT=thermotree/0.1 (contact: you@example.com)
# PHOTON_BASE_URL=https://photon.komoot.io
# PHOTON_USER_AGENT=thermotree/0.1 (contact: you@example.com)

# STAC backends, in priority order. Comma-separated. The first reachable
# backend wins; subsequent backends are tried only on network/HTTP errors
# (timeouts, 5xx, connection failures). A 0-items result or a quality
# rejection from the primary is treated as authoritative and does NOT
# trigger fallback. Valid names: planetary_computer, element84.
#
# STAC_PROVIDERS=planetary_computer,element84
